title: ANP candidate Arbab Muhammad Usman Khan wins PK-71
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Awami National Party (ANP) Candidate Arbab Muhammad Usman Khan won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-71 Peshawar-IV by securing 44,564 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Malik Shahab Hussian who bagged 26,126 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 64.00 per cent.
